article.headline: Tennessee Tech 83, Lipscomb 72
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Darnell Lindsay came off the bench to score 15 points and lift Tennessee Tech to an 83-72 victory over Lipscomb on Tuesday night. Lindsay was one of five players in double figures for the Golden Eagles (2-0), who outscored Lipscomb (1-1) 47-38 in the second half. Zach Bailey added 11 points, and Daniel Northern, Frank Davis and Kevin Murphy scored 10 points each for Tennessee Tech, which shot 52.4 percent (33 of 63) from the field.
